Security Operations Fundamentals > [T2]: Lab - Nessus: Export a detailed report

Export a detailed report of the discovered vulnerabilities

One of the powerful features of Nessus is its reporting capabilities. Nessus can aggregate the report based on one of two factors, either host or the plugin, and it can generate the report in two formats, HTML and CSV.

To do this, open one of your saved scans and click on the Report button.

Figure - zoom in


A new window will show up for you to choose how to structure your report. We will be aggregating the findings based on the host for the demo.

Choose Detailed Vulnerability By Host, then hit the Generate Report button.

Figure - zoom in


Nessus will take time to generate a very detailed and to-the-point HTML report with all the vulnerabilities and information it grabbed during the security scan.

Opening the HTML report, you should see something similar to the screenshot below.
 

Figure - zoom in


Feel free to take a look at this sample report.
